  "response": "The ability to buy a Lamborghini depends on several factors:\n\n1. Salary\n- Average 9-5 workers typically cannot afford a new Lamborghini\n- Base models start around $200,000-$300,000\n- High-end models can cost $500,000+\n\n2. Financial Requirements\n- Would need an annual income of at least $500,000-$1 million\n- Typically requires being in high-paying professions like:\n  - Tech executives\n  - Successful entrepreneurs\n  - Investment bankers\n  - Doctors/surgeons\n  - Professional athletes\n\n3. Potential Scenarios\n- Saving for many years\n- Taking significant financial risks\n- Receiving bonuses/inheritance\n- Financing (though interest rates would be high)\n- Buying used models\n\n4. Practical Considerations\n- Maintenance costs are extremely high\n- Insurance is very expensive\n- Most standard 9-5 jobs don't generate enough disposable income\n\n5. Exceptions\n- Some individuals might achieve this through:\n  - Side businesses\n  - Significant investments\n  - Strict long-term financial planning\n\nGenerally, buying a Lamborghini on a typical 9-5 salary is highly improbable without additional income streams or extraordinary circumstances.",
